cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the application of game theory to the problem of moving target defense in wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also formulates the problem as a stochastic game, which suggests the category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of wireless networks and base stations indicates the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a practical algorithm, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the randomization of cryptographic techniques, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory).
